				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">no, he meant when rendering is off.
<br />
<br />When rendering is on, $3F00 is always the "fill" color (if sprite and BG pixels are transparent, then $3F00 is used)
<br />
<br />When rendering is OFF, then $3F00 is the fill color <em>unless</em> the PPU address is pointed to somewhere in pallet memory.  In which case, whatever the PPU address is pointing to is the fill color.</div>

